  "title": "Principal (International College)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Lead and oversee the college’s day-to-day operations and administrative functions.</li>\n  <li>Supervise, mentor, and support faculty and staff to ensure optimal performance.</li>\n  <li>Oversee curriculum relevance and conduct regular reviews to maintain high educational quality.</li>\n  <li>Recruit and retain high-calibre teachers for the college.</li>\n  <li>Plan and implement orientation programmes for new teachers and students.</li>\n  <li>Foster and maintain positive relationships with parents, guardians, and the wider community.</li>\n  <li>Manage all aspects of student affairs, including strategic planning for recruitment and placement, scholarship administration, and student programmes.</li>\n  <li>Develop and manage the annual budget, ensuring prudent use of resources and financial sustainability.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Postgraduate degree in a relevant field is preferable.</li>\n  <li>NIE-trained, with prior experience in a leadership position within government secondary schools or colleges.</li>\n  <li>Strong familiarity with ‘O’ and ‘A’ Level programmes is preferred.</li>\n  <li>Dynamic, self-motivated, and equipped with strong communication and analytical abilities.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd | EA License No: 20C0270</p>\n<p>EA Personnel No: R22110981| EA Personnel Name: Law Mei Fong</p>",
